Implement enhanced chess prompt with strategic guidance

Key Improvements:
- Expert player persona (2000+ ELO) for higher quality play
- Strategic assessment framework (4 key analysis points)
- Game phase recognition (opening/middlegame/endgame)
- Opponent style analysis from PGN history
- Anti-blunder check before move finalization
- Candidate move evaluation (top 2-3 moves)
- Enhanced reasoning (75-125 words with tactical considerations)

Balanced Approach:
- Manageable token count (~800-1000 tokens)
- Reasonable response length (vs 150-250 words)
- Clear, actionable instructions without overwhelming complexity
- Maintains existing parsing compatibility

Expected Results:
- Better strategic continuity throughout games
- Reduced early king movement issues
- Improved opening play with PGN context
- Enhanced tactical awareness and blunder prevention
- More educational move explanations for users

Summary
Add new i18n strings to support the simple language toggle and its accessibility labels/tooltips.

Scope
- Update src/frontend/locales/en/header.json and de/header.json with:
  - header.language.simpleLabel
  - header.language.simpleDescription
  - header.language.simpleOn (optional)
  - header.language.simpleOff (optional)

Acceptance Criteria
- Keys added in EN and DE with clear, accessible language
- No breaking changes to existing keys

Proposed branch name
- feat/i18n-simple-toggle-strings

Dependencies
- Depends on: Architecture plan (#10)
- Can be parallel to other implementation tasks

performed_via_github_app.description:
SonarQube Cloud (formerly SonarCloud) is a SaaS code analysis tool designed to detect coding issues in 30+ languages, frameworks, and IaC platforms. Your code is checked against an extensive set of rules that cover many attributes of code, such as maintainability, reliability, and security issues, on each merge/pull request.

For those requiring US-based hosting, [SonarQube Cloud US](https://sonarqube.us/) offers the perfect alternative. If you need data residency outside the US or within the EU, [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/) with this GitHub app is the ideal solution.

SonarQube Cloud integrates seamlessly into your GitHub workflow and provides clear guidance for resolving any code quality and security issues detected. The majority of popular languages can be analyzed automatically; no configuration is required!

With [SonarQube Cloud](https://sonarcloud.io/github), you get:

-   Fast, precise static analysis and feedback on your code
    
-   Support for popular languages, frameworks, and IaC tools
    
-   Free analysis for open-source projects and private projects up to max 50k LoC
    
-   Automatic analysis of pull requests and branches with results reported inline
    
-   IDE Support with [SonarQube for IDE](https://www.sonarsource.com/products/sonarlint/) integration

pull_request.title: Fix Ctrl-C segfaults in sage.libs.gap
pull_request.body:
Replace cysignals' `sig_on()` and `sig_off()` with custom `gap_sig_on()` and `gap_sig_off()` wrappers that use GAP's own `SIGINT` handling. This fixes an uncommon, but ultimately reproducible segfault when Ctrl-C is used to interrupt a GAP computation.

In concert with https://github.com/sagemath/sage/pull/40594 this has allowed `sage/libs/gap/element.pyx` to pass many thousands of test iterations.

Fixes:

* https://github.com/sagemath/sage/issues/40598

@@ -886,6 +886,19 @@ def ensure_interruptible_after(seconds: float, max_wait_after_interrupt: float =
     except AlarmInterrupt as e:

         alarm_raised = True
+    except KeyboardInterrupt as e:
+        from sage.libs.gap.util import GAPError
+        if isinstance(e.__cause__, GAPError):
+            # To handle SIGALRM in GAP we install its SIGINT handler
+            # as the SIGALRM handler. When it gets Ctrl-C, we turn the
+            # resulting GAPError into a KeyboardInterrupt... but
+            # there's no real way to distinguish the SIGALRM case
+            # (doctesting) from the SIGINT case (interactive Ctrl-C)
+            # except for context.
+            e.__traceback__ = None
+            alarm_raised = True
+        else:
+            raise
